learningOutcomes.en:
Knowledge and Understanding
• critically discuss and assess the role of negotiations in different organisations;
• describe and evaluate a range of specific negotiation methodologies, techniques and tools; 
• critically discuss and assess the practical issues involved in developing negotiation models and systems;
• describe and evaluate appropriate organisational conditions for conducting negotiations; 
 
Subject-specific skills
• design and analyse simple negotiations; 
• elicit relevant information needed for negotiation analytics models; 
• conduct analyses of negotiations with multiple objectives;
• construct and use analytical models to support multi-party negotiations.

prerequisites.en:
Recommended prerequisites: Foundations
of entrepreneurship; Sustainable Entrepreneurship, Markets, and Systems change;
Social Innovation.
